<subSubSection id="E40338C1685012E1377706860E2F3684" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="notes">
<paragraph id="9B92053B0EA29275E1954CC9EA519093" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D6D07C5E1D737A8A0AC8294F9DB00D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="F8C9033C4B71EC9A1AE559D56214DBB7" authorityName="S. H. Huang &amp; Y. M. Shui" authorityYear="1994" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia malipoensis" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="malipoensis">
<emphasis id="90364DA8B6C2BCE2770929C6904A2BE5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Begonia malipoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described for the first time in 1994 and its type locality is Douchidian of Malipo Xian, Yunnan Province (
<bibRefCitation id="9112496F1554A97421CBA91D2F1F52AA" author="Huang, SH" journalOrPublisher="Yunnan Zhi Wu Yan Jiu" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="333 - 342" refId="B19" refString="Huang, SH, Shui, YM, 1994. New taxa of Begonia from Yunnan. Yunnan Zhi Wu Yan Jiu 16 (4): 333 - 342" title="New taxa of Begonia from Yunnan." volume="16" year="1994">Huang and Shui 1994</bibRefCitation>
). In the wild, it grows closely with 
<taxonomicName id="BC78B7B2969E7F1849063DBC0EC55D57" genus="B." lsidName="B. hemsleyana" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="hemsleyana">
<emphasis id="4C9BFFE9BF93DD0C8B1AD391D04552CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. hemsleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hook.f. (
<bibRefCitation id="E4BB26F6DEB1D78822910E64FEED618D" author="Curtis, W" journalOrPublisher="Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/14253page/212/mode/1up" refId="B8" refString="Curtis, W, Hooker, JD, Hooker, WJ, Prain, D, Stapf, O, 1899. Curtis's Botanical Magazine 125: Tab. 7685. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/14253page/212/mode/1up" title="Curtis's Botanical Magazine 125: Tab. 7685." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/14253page/212/mode/1up" year="1899">Curtis et al. 1899</bibRefCitation>
) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E52F966D282B2EA601CCB872820B529A" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Begonia x malipoensis and its parents (B. hemsleyana and B. versicolor) (Photos by Daike Tian) A habitat of a natural hybrid zone of B. versicolor x B. hemsleyana B-E variation of B. x malipoensis F B. hemsleyana G, H B. versicolor with variegated and pure green leaves I, J comparison of B. x malipoensis (middle two leaves) and its parents B. hemsleyana (left) and B. versicolor (right two leaves) (I adaxial view J abaxial view)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.153.50805.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/432256" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">12F</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="3A0C54C7E14F07389743E8E73B7EB6F7" genus="B." lsidName="B. versicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis id="CA3246B692C8AAAC4C5B211F19AE6F73" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. versicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Irmsch (
<bibRefCitation id="695A8C66E819CE962660B060799BB8B5" author="Irmscher, E" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Institut fuer Allgemeine Botanik in Hamburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="431 - 557" refId="B23" refString="Irmscher, E, 1939. Die Begoniaceen Chinas und ihre Bedeutung fur die Frage der Formbildung in polymorphen Sippen. Mitteilungen aus dem Institut fuer Allgemeine Botanik in Hamburg 10: 431 - 557" title="Die Begoniaceen Chinas und ihre Bedeutung fur die Frage der Formbildung in polymorphen Sippen." volume="10" year="1939">Irmscher 1939</bibRefCitation>
) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="42B788B2D53B57257FD06BEB183BB3E7" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Begonia x malipoensis and its parents (B. hemsleyana and B. versicolor) (Photos by Daike Tian) A habitat of a natural hybrid zone of B. versicolor x B. hemsleyana B-E variation of B. x malipoensis F B. hemsleyana G, H B. versicolor with variegated and pure green leaves I, J comparison of B. x malipoensis (middle two leaves) and its parents B. hemsleyana (left) and B. versicolor (right two leaves) (I adaxial view J abaxial view)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.153.50805.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/432256" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">12E, F</figureCitation>
). Later, Daike Tian (
<bibRefCitation id="5B41F68A3A913C26E770C39E08518F4D" author="Tian, DK" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" refId="B39" refString="Tian, DK, 1999. Horticultural Study on Begoniaversicolor. Kunming Institute of Botany, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Master Thesis, Kunming. [in Chinese with English abstract]" title="Horticultural Study on Begoniaversicolor. Kunming Institute of Botany, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Master Thesis, Kunming. [in Chinese with English abstract]" year="1999">Tian 1999</bibRefCitation>
) conducted field surveys on the diversity of 
<taxonomicName id="F2A942D546CDC25D8868733933B1E180" genus="B." lsidName="B. versicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis id="D5B7D404F72A0384AF8B3D5E925F679B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. versicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in southeastern Yunnan and found a few plants of 
<taxonomicName id="3263A698A681BE325F4F43C9B4CDA6C0" genus="B." lsidName="B. malipoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="malipoensis">
<emphasis id="E862A5FB48E156C0F635EB2CEB6F62DF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. malipoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the same locality and at Daweishan National Nature Reserve of Pingbian County, Yunnan Province. Based on the very limited number of individuals and intermediate morphology between 
<taxonomicName id="C079E500E8DB90319437341A499C515B" genus="B." lsidName="B. hemsleyana" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="hemsleyana">
<emphasis id="BAF7A4164F4D71B5047DF6C4A238B47F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. hemsleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AA51AFB30E222A8D50718159CA4FBCFE" genus="B." lsidName="B. versicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis id="B2465CDAB723AA169B1B92266B13084E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. versicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2584A5461ACE8EB8DA5CAC0F074A8BE6" genus="B." lsidName="B. malipoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="malipoensis">
<emphasis id="FECC429CE8497655CB48462866498C83" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. malipoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a natural hybrid and this supposition was confirmed by artificial cross experiments (
<bibRefCitation id="6A30F7DD642D4288DA5C6A73D186EB44" author="Tian, DK" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" refId="B39" refString="Tian, DK, 1999. Horticultural Study on Begoniaversicolor. Kunming Institute of Botany, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Master Thesis, Kunming. [in Chinese with English abstract]" title="Horticultural Study on Begoniaversicolor. Kunming Institute of Botany, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Master Thesis, Kunming. [in Chinese with English abstract]" year="1999">Tian 1999</bibRefCitation>
). From natural hybrids, one type, with densely white-spotted leaves, was selected as a new cultivar, 
<taxonomicName id="CB9F0EDA2E19958E8B46355D76DB07A9" genus="B." lsidName="B." pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="genus">B.</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="8EEE783EA548FC232BACEC2A0670B49D" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="70829C06DEB839D24F678C5B47A8A846" genus="B." lsidName="malipoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="malipoensis">malipoensis</taxonomicName>
'White 
<normalizedToken id="AC25AAC63016CCA782ACAF72B3FD1F5A" originalValue="Snowâ€™">Snow'</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="DEE972B4498F14805E508136A3E42F00" author="Tian, DK" journalOrPublisher="Yuan Yi Xue Bao" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="186 - 186" refId="B40" refString="Tian, DK, Li, JX, Guan, KY, 2001. New Begonia varieties -'Kunming Bird', 'Kang-er' and 'White Snow'. Yuan Yi Xue Bao 28 (2): 186 - 186" title="New Begonia varieties - ' Kunming Bird', ' Kang-er' and ' White Snow'." volume="28" year="2001">Tian et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The hybrid status of 
<taxonomicName id="A2AD0342ACB54471F93B6AC24F3583B2" genus="B." lsidName="B." pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="genus">B.</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="B099BB49E86552AB7ECBA52A9D66DA1E" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="722808DB6E6EFFF1D3FC5F72915980ED" genus="B." lsidName="malipoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="malipoensis">malipoensis</taxonomicName>
was further supported by molecular evidence (
<bibRefCitation id="A9B19FE2C094A2B707C75A1D4C4B521D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pld.2018.06.002" author="Tian, DK" journalOrPublisher="Plant Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="75 - 90" refId="B43" refString="Tian, DK, Xiao, Y, Tong, Y, Fu, NF, Liu, QQ, Li, C, 2018. Diversity and conservation of Chinese wild begonias. Plant Diversity 40 (3): 75 - 90, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pld.2018.06.002" title="Diversity and conservation of Chinese wild begonias." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pld.2018.06.002" volume="40" year="2018">Tian et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
